        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pinpoint Tests - Interior Lighting</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test A: The Interior Lamps Are Inoperative</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Under normal operation, voltage is fed from the power distribution center (PDC) fuse 28 (10A) to the
                interior lamp through circuit 54 (LG/YE). When a door is opened, ground is provided by the door ajar
                switch to the interior lamp through circuit 159 (RD/PK).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>An open in circuit 54 (LG/YE) or 159 (RD/PK)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>An open fuse</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Interior lamp</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Bulb</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <table id="t1702050" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>PINPOINT TEST A: THE INTERIOR LAMPS ARE INOPERATIVE</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A1 CHECK CIRCUIT 54 (LG/YE) FOR VOLTAGE</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Open the LH and RH doors.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                            Interior Lamp C981.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between interior lamp C981, circuit 54 (LG/YE) and
                                            ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0024056.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A2.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>VERIFY the power distribution center (PDC) fuse 28 (10A) is OK. If OK, REPAIR
                                    circuit 54 (LG/YE) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A2 CHECK CIRCUIT 159 (RD/PK) FOR AN OPEN</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between interior lamp C981, circuit 159 (RD/PK) and
                                            ground
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0024057.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 5 ohms?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSPECT the interior lamp bulb for an open. If OK, INSTALL a new lamp. TEST the
                                    system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 159 (RD/PK) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test B: The Interior Lamps Stay On Continuously</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Under normal operation, when a door is opened, ground is provided by the door ajar switch to the
                interior lamp through circuit 159 (RD/PK).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>A short to ground in circuit 159 (RD/PK)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Door ajar switch</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <table id="t1702051" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>PINPOINT TEST B: THE INTERIOR LAMPS STAY ON CONTINUOUSLY</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">B1 CHECK THE LH DOOR AJAR SWITCH</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>LH Door Ajar Switch C526.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Observe the interior lamps.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Are the interior lamps OFF?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new LH door ajar switch. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to B2.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">B2 CHECK THE RH DOOR AJAR SWITCH</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>RH Door Ajar Switch C602.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Observe the interior lamps.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Are the interior lamps OFF?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new RH door ajar switch. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 159 (RD/PK) for a short to ground. TEST the system for normal
                                    operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test C: The Interior Lamps Do Not Turn ON With One Door Open</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Under normal operation, when a door is opened, ground is provided by the door ajar switch to the
                interior lamp through circuit 159 (RD/PK).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>An open in circuit 159 (RD/PK)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Door ajar switch</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <table id="t1702052" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>PINPOINT TEST C: THE INTERIOR LAMPS DO NOT TURN ON WITH ONE DOOR OPEN</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">C1 CHECK THE INOPERATIVE DOOR AJAR SWITCH</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>Inoperative Door Ajar Switch (RH) C602
                                            or (LH) C526.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Connect a fused jumper wire between the inoperative door ajar switch (RH)
                                            C602 or (LH) C526, circuit 159 (RD/PK) and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0024058.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Are the interior lamps ON?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new RH or LH door ajar switch. TEST the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 159 (RD/PK) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
